Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.54,0:01:01.54,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\c&HE8D8EA&\bord0\blur0.6\b} Toyotama Prison, July 3, 1945 {昭和20年7月3日\N豐多摩刑務所}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.72,0:01:18.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Dear...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.98,0:01:21.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Dear!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.23,0:01:24.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, Ikue? {幾枝}\NYou came to pick me up?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:24.81,0:01:26.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Is the house safe? {/alright/survived the bombings}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.15,0:01:28.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. Everyone is in good health.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.53,0:01:31.07,Default,,0,0,0,,I see. I'm glad, so glad.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.07,0:01:34.66,Default,,0,0,0,,I've caused you so much trouble. {to cause someone trouble; to burden someone} \NBut you've nothing to worry about now.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.99,0:01:36.62,Default,,0,0,0,,So, shall we go?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.33,0:01:39.45,Narrator,,0,0,0,,It was exactly this yukata-clad man {この浴衣がけの男こそ後年民衆の偉大な指導者としご 知られるようになる“戸田城聖”その人ごあった}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.45,0:01:45.59,Narrator,,0,0,0,,who would later come to be known as Toda Josei, \Nthe great commander and guide of the people. {I can't find any english established translation for "民衆の偉大な指導者" except "the great master, the transmitter of the teachings, the commander and guide" in one of academic works}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.59,0:01:50.76,Narrator,,0,0,0,,However, at that time, \NToda's name was barely known to anyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.26,0:01:52.93,Narrator,,0,0,0,,He was only known to the authorities
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.93,0:01:58.56,Narrator,,0,0,0,,as a criminal offender, charged with a violation \Nof Peace Preservation Law and lese-majesty
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.56,0:02:03.14,Narrator,,0,0,0,,for his refusal to worship a Shinto amulet \Nand staying faithful to Buddha. {actually "in order to protect the purity of his faith" but I think this is more accurate in accordance with what happened irl} {信仰の純粋性を守り、神札を祀ることを拒否したことで治安維持法違反と不敬罪による 刑事被告人として当局に知られているにすぎなかった} {TLDR: military was trying to shut up everyone who was speaking out against the war, by making them accept state shintoism though accepting a shinto talisman - toda refused}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.77,0:02:05.31,Default,,0,0,0,,So it was this bad? {assumed he means bombings}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.94,0:02:08.32,Default,,0,0,0,,And what about Morimoto's place?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.32,0:02:10.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Burned down in an air raid, \Nso they moved to the countryside...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.78,0:02:12.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, what about Kondo? {近藤}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.28,0:02:14.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Their house as well...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.16,0:02:18.91,Thought,,0,0,0,,Such a destructive endeavor... \NYet they are looking to prolong it? {/For how long will they keep doing it?}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.91,0:02:21.45,Thought,,0,0,0,,Has this war made anyone happier?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.87,0:02:25.79,Thought,,0,0,0,,Peace and happiness are supposed to be \Nthe shared aspirations of all the humankind. {平和と幸福は人々の共通の願いであるはずだ}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.79,0:02:29.21,Thought,,0,0,0,,But instead, once every ten years or so, we find ourselves
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.21,0:02:32.30,Thought,,0,0,0,,plunged into a war where the nation's survival is at stake. {それなのに 十年に一度といっでよいほど国運を賭しての 戦争に突入している}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.30,0:02:36.76,Thought,,0,0,0,,Whatever it takes, we must steer Japan \Naway from this path. {こんな日本の運命を何としても転換しなければ}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.56,0:02:46.35,Default,,0,0,0,,If anything, the Americans got some fine iron \Nin their firebomb shells!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.35,0:02:49.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. That iron is top-notch{ quality}! {あの鉄の質はべらぼうなもんだ}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.27,0:02:52.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I even made a shovel with it once \Nand it worked wonders! {あれでシャベルを作ってみたがすごいのができる!}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.28,0:02:56.20,Default,,0,0,0,,If you need a kitchen knife, \Nyou can make five or six from a single shell! {包丁だったら一つの殻で5~6丁は取れるかな?}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.20,0:02:57.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Why be so stingy?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.74,0:02:59.03,Default,,0,0,0,,You can get away with all ten!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.45,0:03:04.00,Thought,,0,0,0,,The masses remain resilient \Nno matter the times they're facing. {庶民大衆というのはいつの時代にあってもたくましいな - I think he means "would adapt/survive/find a way through in any era"}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.71,0:03:05.58,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.63,0:03:19.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Harajuku! Harajuku!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.05,0:03:22.81,Thought,,0,0,0,,I see. The Meiji Shrine. {そうか明治神宮を}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.31,0:03:24.81,Thought,,0,0,0,,What foolish thinking. {愚かしいことだ}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.81,0:03:29.36,Thought,,0,0,0,,Without revering the true Buddha's ways, \Nthey expect a divine protection from all deities at once. {正法を尊ばずして諸天善神の加護があるはずがない - I think he means "they're desperate from war, hence looking for protection both from buddha deities and shinto deities, but that doesn't work this way"}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.94,0:03:33.23,Thought,,0,0,0,,Ignorance towards religion was the faulty notion
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.23,0:03:37.49,Thought,,0,0,0,,that propelled Japan into this reckless war in the preceding years. {宗教への無知が誤った思想が日本をここまで無謀な戦争へと駆り立ててしまったのだ}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.49,0:03:40.32,Thought,,0,0,0,,And because of that, President Makiguchi... {https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tsunesabur%C5%8D_Makiguchi}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.91,0:03:44.91,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Imprisoned on the same ideological offense charges as Toda, President Makiguchi
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.91,0:03:45.50,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\fade(300,400)\c&HFDF1FF&\bord0\blur0.5\b} Tsunesaburo Makiguchi, founder of Soka Gakkai {創価学会初代会長 牧口常三郎}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.91,0:03:47.87,Narrator,,0,0,0,,was subjected to the harsh interrogations and malnutrition. {戸田と同じく思想犯で逮捕された牧口会長は過酷な取り調べと栄養失調がもとで}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.87,0:03:51.42,Narrator,,0,0,0,,And on November 18th of 1944,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.84,0:03:53.75,Narrator,,0,0,0,,he passed away in his prison cell. {昭和19年11月18日 獄中にて逝去した}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.34,0:03:57.38,Narrator,,0,0,0,,He was 73 years old. {73歳の高齢ごあった}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.38,0:04:01.85,Thought,,0,0,0,,Makiguchi-sensei, you can trust me to make every effort... {this toda will definitely...}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.31,0:04:08.94,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the only part of the town \Nthat survived the fires somehow. {この辺りだけどうにか焼けずに残っているんですよ}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.94,0:04:13.19,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm glad it did. I still have a home to go back to. {ありがたいことだ帰る家があるってことは}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.61,0:04:18.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Dear, please watch your step.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.57,0:04:19.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Dear!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.54,0:04:32.54,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\c&H060505&\3c&H1F221B&\bord4\blur1}Toda {戸田 }
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.25,0:04:34.84,Thought,,0,0,0,,The Great Buddha, {principal object of worship at a temple (usu. a buddha or bodhisattva); principal image; idol - "Gohonzon is a generic term for a venerated religious object in Japanese Buddhism. It may take the form of a scroll or statuary." - I wanted to make it "my dear lord" but it may be a scroll or some other inanimate object later so leaving this for now} {fuck it, buddha it is}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.01,0:04:38.01,Thought,,0,0,0,,I have finally returned.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.27,0:04:48.94,Thought,,0,0,0,,He's so emaciated... {to become thin; to lose weight; to reduce (one's) weight; to slim}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.69,0:04:54.15,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}{南無妙法蓮華経 } Nam Myoho Renge Kyo...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.15,0:04:57.32,Thought,,0,0,0,,But at least, he managed to return home safely...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.19,0:05:02.70,Thought,,0,0,0,,The Great Buddha{Gohonzon-sama}, thank you so much.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.33,0:05:08.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Dear, the air-raid alert is on. {警戒警報}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.58,0:05:10.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Well-well.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.33,0:05:15.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Just when I got home, there's an air raid? {やれやれ帰ってきたかと思うと 今度は空襲か}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.09,0:05:16.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Dear, let's go to the shelter. {防空壕}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.71,0:05:19.05,Default,,0,0,0,,No, I'm staying here.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.05,0:05:22.84,Default,,0,0,0,,It's out of question! \NWhat if a bomb lands right here? {/What if an air raid bomb lands right here?}{lit: receive a direct hit from ...}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.84,0:05:24.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on, dear, hurry now!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.30,0:05:27.39,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll stay here to protect the Great Buddha{Gohonzon-sama}.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.39,0:05:28.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.64,0:05:32.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Ikue, make haste and leave.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.52,0:05:37.36,Default,,0,0,0,,The darker the night gets, \Nthe closer the dawn must be. {闇が深ければ深いほど暁は近いはずだ}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.78,0:05:40.03,Thought,,0,0,0,,The Great Buddha, Daishonin-sama, {Gohonzon-sama, Daishonin-sama,} {Nichiren Daishōnin (日蓮大聖人,\NGreat Sage Nichiren)}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.40,0:05:44.66,Thought,,0,0,0,,I will disseminate the law of righteousness \Nand bring the salvation to the masses,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.66,0:05:47.62,Thought,,0,0,0,,to ensure that the Common Path is achieved. {very liberal interpretation, but kosen rufu would be impossible to use without a TL note; https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kosen-rufu}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.62,0:05:56.17,Thought,,0,0,0,,If we want to pursue the Common Path, \NSoka Kyoiku Gakkai has to be rebuilt. {might change to the Value-Creating Educational Society} {創価教育学会を再建しなければならない}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.17,0:06:00.26,Narrator,,0,0,0,,"The first step towards that would be \Nan establishment of an economic basis." {“それにはまず経済的な基盤を確立しなければ"と}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.26,0:06:05.89,Narrator,,0,0,0,,With such thoughts, Toda immediately directed \Nhis every effort towards rebuilding his business. {戸田は日を待たずして事業の再建へ向けて行動を起こした}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.72,0:06:11.64,Default,,0,0,0,,And that is the financial statement \Nof the business you've entrusted us with. {それが戸田さんからお預かりしていた事業の決算書です}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.02,0:06:16.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Is this bottom number written in black? Or is it... {この一番下の数字は黒ですか? それとも…} {bottom line is net value, black means profit, red means loss}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.27,0:06:17.44,Default,,0,0,0,,It's in red.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.65,0:06:19.03,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.57,0:06:23.07,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Having learned that the business he used to run {himself }
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.07,0:06:27.12,Narrator,,0,0,0,,had collapsed entirely \Nduring his two-year-long imprisonment, Toda {入獄中の2年間にすべて破たんして しまったことを知った戸田は}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.12,0:06:31.08,Narrator,,0,0,0,,decided to start anew \Nwith his correspondence courses business, {新たに通信教授の出版事業を始めることにし }
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.08,0:06:33.25,Narrator,,0,0,0,,and the preparations were set in motion. {その準備に着手した}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.96,0:06:35.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Which brings me to...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.50,0:06:40.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Wouldn't it be possible for us to receive a small loan
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.38,0:06:43.05,Default,,0,0,0,,with this fire insurance certificate\N as a collateral? {この火災保険証書を担保に少々都合してもらぇないだろうか?}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.05,0:06:45.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Sure. Fine by me.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.13,0:06:46.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.59,0:06:47.85,Default,,0,0,0,,I am truly grateful!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.68,0:06:54.98,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Once a print shop was set up and paper for it procured \Nwith money raised from his old friend,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.98,0:06:59.11,Narrator,,0,0,0,,at last, the reopening of his business was all but ready. {well-ordered; in good order; well-featured; well-regulated} {旧知の友人から資金を調達し印刷所や紙などの手配をつけてようやく\N事業再開の準備が整った時}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.07,0:07:08.62,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\fade(200,0)\bord0\blur0.5\c&HF8E6F4&} August 6th, Hiroshima
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.15,0:07:08.62,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\fade(200,0)\bord0\blur0.5\c&HF8E6F4&} August 9th, Nagasaki
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.62,0:07:15.54,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b0}After pondering deeply the general trends of the world \Nand the actual conditions obtaining to our empire today, {朕󠄁深ク世界ノ大勢ト帝󠄁國ノ現狀トニ鑑ミ}{jewel voice speech, translation from wikipedia}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.20,0:07:16.62,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\fade(300,0)\bord0\blur0.5\c&HF7EFF1&} August 15, 1945: End of war {昭和20年8月15日 終戦}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.54,0:07:23.05,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fade(0,200)\b0}we have decided to effect a settlement of the present situation by resorting to an extraordinary measure... {非常ノ措置ヲ以テ時局ヲ收拾セムト欲シ茲ニ忠良ナル爾臣民ニ吿ク} {the last part is off but I can't be bothered}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.62,0:07:23.05,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\fade(0,500)\bord0\blur0.5\c&HFCF8FF&} Japan unconditionally surrenders \Nto the Allied Forces, ending World War II {日本、連合軍に無条件降伏 第二次世界大戦終結}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.05,0:07:24.30,Default,,0,0,0,,"In their present existence,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.30,0:07:28.22,Default,,0,0,0,,the clergy of Japan, as well as the laity revering them, are transforming this country... {full text: https://gosho-search.sokanet.jp/page.php?n=1450 ; mainly taking translation from https://www.nichirenlibrary.org/en/wnd-1/Content/100 without the text he omittted} {されば今の日本国の諸僧等は、又、在家の人々は}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.22,0:07:32.26,Default,,0,0,0,,...In addition to agonies unknown in previous ages, will be swarmed by a foreign power. {先代になき大苦を受くる上他国より責めらるべし }
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.47,0:07:34.10,Default,,0,0,0,,This is due solely
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.10,0:07:38.10,Default,,0,0,0,,to the workings of deities like Brahma, Shakra, and the gods of the Sun and Moon..." {此は偏に梵天、帝釈、日月等の御はからひなり  }
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.56,0:07:43.36,Thought,,0,0,0,,Nichiren Daishonin's prophecy came true all too exact. {日蓮大聖人の予言はあまりにも厳しく的中してしまった}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.03,0:07:46.40,Thought,,0,0,0,,By oppressing those who believe in true Buddhism
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.40,0:07:50.41,Thought,,0,0,0,,and imposing a faulty national Shintoism upon the people,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.41,0:07:52.49,Thought,,0,0,0,,they brought about the ruin of our country. {誤った国家神道を国民に押し付けてきたことが国を滅ぼしてしまったのだ}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.79,0:07:55.75,Thought,,0,0,0,,But who could've possibly seen this coming? {unsure, maybe "who knows about it now"} {だがこのことを誰が知っているだろうか}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.37,0:07:58.46,Thought,,0,0,0,,More than ever,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.00,0:08:03.71,Thought,,0,0,0,,the time has come for Nichiren Daishonin's \Ngreat {Buddhist }Dharma to start shining. {no clue what's this 大仏法, assumed his school of buddhism, though could be that it's another name for nichirin himself, like "the great buddha"? https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nichiren_Buddhism is actually a thing but it's not called daibuppo} {今まさしく日蓮大聖人の大仏法が光り輝く時が到来したのだ}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.71,0:08:08.51,Thought,,0,0,0,,Apart from this moment, the Common Path \Nwon't have a chance to take off ever again. {この時を外して未来永劫に広宣流布の機会はない - actually just "there won't be an opportunity/chance of kosen rufu forevermore" and I think he means this}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.51,0:08:10.93,Thought,,0,0,0,,We can by no means let this chance slip! {to miss (e.g. a chance); to lose time} {I don't like using two "chance" in a row but everything else doesn't quite do it for me}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.10,0:08:15.98,Narrator,,0,0,0,,The Allied Occupation Forces \Nwere promptly deployed to Japan. {いち早く連合国の占領軍が日本に進駐}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.47,0:08:18.52,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\bord0\blur0.5\c&HFCF8FF&} General MacArthur, Supreme Commander of the Allied Forces {連合国軍最高司令官 マッカーサー元帥}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.98,0:08:20.60,Narrator,,0,0,0,,All political, economic, educational, and other internal functions of a defeated Japan
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.60,0:08:23.52,Narrator,,0,0,0,,were placed under strict supervision of GHQ. {敗戦国日本の政治・経済・教育などすべての機能がGHQの監督下に置かれた}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.52,0:08:23.52,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\bord0\blur0.5\c&HFFEAEA&}Hibiya GHQ (General Headquarters of the Allied Powers) {日比谷 GHQ (連合国軍総司令部)}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.52,0:08:26.53,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\bord0\blur0.5\c&HFCF8FF&} {\c&HF5F0FE&}Kamiosaki, Shinagawa Ward, Tokyo \NNihon Shogakkan Publishing Office {can't find anything at all about this one apart from that it was toda's operational base immediately after the war; there's a company with a similar namem here's excerpt from its wiki: The company 's name comes from the fact that when it was founded, its main business was publishing educational books for elementary school students .} {品川区 上大崎\N日本正学館・事務所}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.53,0:08:30.74,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\bord3\blur0.5\c&H151319&\3c&H6C88A2&} Nihon Shogakkan {I'm confused, they use "学" for previous sign but 學 here, it's just an outdated version tho so whatever}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.99,0:08:27.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Watch your back!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.86,0:08:29.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah! It's here, here!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.74,0:08:31.87,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.87,0:08:34.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, this is when things finally get busy. {さあ いよいよ忙しぐなるぞ }\NOkumura-kun!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.99,0:08:36.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Is everything ready? {奥村君準備はいいかい?}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.29,0:08:37.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.25,0:08:38.75,Default,,0,0,0,,All right! There it is! {そら 来たぞ}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.75,0:08:41.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. You're through to Nihon Shogakkan. {はぃ 日本正学館でごさいます}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.83,0:08:43.63,Default,,0,0,0,,You'd like to make an order? {ご注文でごさぃますね}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.63,0:08:49.13,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Mere five days after the end of war, \NToda's correspondence courses business started.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.13,0:08:51.59,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\bord3\blur0.5\c&H232438&\3c&HD0C7DD&} English / Mathematics / Physical studies \NNihon Shogakkan {英語·數學·物象 - no clue what's the last one}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.22,0:08:51.59,Default,,0,0,0,,They're here!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.10,0:08:54.60,Default,,0,0,0,,This much!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.60,0:08:59.14,Default,,0,0,0,,It's only natural! We've put an ad \Nin a nationwide newspaper. {そりゃそうだよ 全国版の新聞に広告を出したんだがら}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.14,0:09:01.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Good. Let's divvy those up and process them. {よし 手分けして整理しよう!}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.06,0:09:03.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.98,0:09:05.86,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Besides the correspondence courses
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.86,0:09:08.82,Narrator,,0,0,0,,in mathematics and physics, aimed at young men and women, {boys and girls} {少年少女を対象にした数学と物理の通信教授に加え}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.82,0:09:10.74,Narrator,,0,0,0,,in anticipation of the "English{ language} boom,"
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.74,0:09:14.45,Narrator,,0,0,0,,they were among the first to {devise and }publish a well-received academic course of English. {英語ブームの到来を予想していち早く企画出版した英語講座が評判を呼び}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.45,0:09:17.50,Narrator,,0,0,0,,The business was steadily taking off. {事業は着実に軌道に乗っていった}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.95,0:09:21.46,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\bord0\blur0.5\c&HF9EFFC&} Kanda Ward (nowadays Chiyoda Ward), Nishi-Kanda {神田区 (現千代田区) 西神田}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.50,0:09:21.46,Narrator,,0,0,0,,And then, in October, Toda moved \Ninto the citadel of the publishing world - {そして10月戸田は出版界の本拠地神田に進出し}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.46,0:09:24.79,Narrator,,0,0,0,,the Kanda Ward, where inside \Na three-story building in Nishi-Kanda, {西神田の3階建てのビルに }
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.54,0:09:26.55,Sign,,0,0,0,,Nihon Shogakkan {日本正学館}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.79,0:09:30.13,Narrator,,0,0,0,,the office of the publishing company \NNihon Shogakkan was officially opened. {出版社“日本正学館”の事務所を正式に開設したのである}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.13,0:09:34.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Tell you what, Sensei. \NThat's one fine lot you've found. {それにしても先生まったくうまいところが見つかったものですね}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.55,0:09:37.14,Default,,0,0,0,,One can only ascribe it to a divine grace. {功徳としか言いようがないですね}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.31,0:09:40.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh? Yam today as well? {おつ 今日も芋かい?}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.39,0:09:45.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I'd like to say so, too, \Nbut I can't really call yam a divine grace. {not really sure what he means} {ま私もそうだけど芋ではあまり功徳とは言えんな}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.11,0:09:50.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah? Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.03,0:09:55.53,Default,,0,0,0,,However, it is beyond doubt that this building \Nwas a gift from Buddha{Gohonzon-sama} himself.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.53,0:09:59.08,Default,,0,0,0,,For my devotion to the Lotus Sutra, \NI've been thrown into prison for two whole years, {法華経のために牢屋にぶち込まれて丸2年間}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.08,0:10:03.25,Default,,0,0,0,,which I spent fighting in deadly agony, \Nhence this divine reward. {死ぬ苦しみで戦ってきたその功徳なんだよ}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.25,0:10:06.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know in which way will this building serve us in the future,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.54,0:10:08.63,Default,,0,0,0,,but I'm sure only good things will come out of it. {probably refers to him opening the department of soka gakkai on the second floor of it later} {この建物が今後どんな働きをするかきっとすごいことになるよ}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.63,0:10:10.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's all take good care of it. {みんな 大事に使おうじゃないか}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.59,0:10:11.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.09,0:10:11.59,Overlap,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.47,0:10:21.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, thank you for stopping by. \NI'm counting on you to do your best now. {いやあ 訪ねてくれてありがとう じゃしっかり頼みますよ - unsure what's this last part about}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.39,0:10:24.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, I won't let you down. \NThank you very much.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.23,0:10:26.61,Narrator,,0,0,0,,The office of Nihon Shogakkan in Nishi-Kanda
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.61,0:10:28.73,Narrator,,0,0,0,,became the main operational base for Soka Gakkai. {/Society}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.73,0:10:32.28,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Upon learning that Chairman Toda was alive and well, many pre-war members
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.28,0:10:34.57,Narrator,,0,0,0,,gradually started flocking to there. {戦前からの会員が次第に集まってくるようになった}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.07,0:10:36.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Toda-sensei!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.87,0:10:39.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Sensei!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.46,0:10:45.46,Default,,0,0,0,,If it isn't Yamadaira-kun!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.46,0:10:48.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Yamadaira Chuhei... has just returned!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.88,0:10:49.67,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.01,0:10:55.80,Default,,0,0,0,,How wonderful that you've returned alive!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.80,0:10:59.18,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm glad! Really glad! \NIt must've been awfully hard for you! {actually "thank you for your hard work" but not here}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.01,0:11:04.98,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Yamadaira Chuhei went to war as a mobilized student, but managed to return safely. {学徒動員で出征し 無事帰還した山平忠平}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.98,0:11:10.90,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Thus, men sent to the battlefield, one after another, were trickling back to Toda. {not sure what to make of 赴く} {こうして戦地に赴いていた者も 一人二人と戸田のもとにと…}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.86,0:11:17.07,Default,,0,0,0,,I see. He is five already?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.16,0:11:19.78,Default,,0,0,0,,So? Did you like it?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.78,0:11:20.58,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.58,0:11:22.58,Default,,0,0,0,,No need to be shy about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.58,0:11:25.58,Default,,0,0,0,,We still have plenty more. \NFeel free to take some home. {まだたくさんぁるがらな後で持って帰りなさぃ}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.58,0:11:26.62,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.67,0:11:32.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, day after day, all I think about is death! {もう毎日每日死ぬことばかり考えています}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.55,0:11:34.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I should probably take this child with me... {いっそこの子を道連れにして…}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.84,0:11:39.35,Default,,0,0,0,,What's this nonsense you're saying? \NHow will your death help things? {何をばかなことを言っているんだ 死んでどうなるというんだ}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.35,0:11:51.69,Default,,0,0,0,,"Human life is far more precious and important \Nthan all the treasures in the universe." {人の命というのは宇宙にあるすべての財宝よりもはるかに尊く大切なものなんだと}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.69,0:11:54.44,Default,,0,0,0,,That's what Daishonin taught us.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.44,0:11:58.91,Default,,0,0,0,,It would be outrageous to take that life for granted. {その命を粗末にしようなんてとんでもないことです}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.62,0:12:02.45,Narrator,,0,0,0,,After this war, countless people, including the Society members,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.45,0:12:07.62,Narrator,,0,0,0,,dwelt in the depths of despair, having lost their husbands or families to the fire during air raids. {この戦争で幾人かの会員もまた空襲で家を焼かれ夫や家族を矢い失意のどん底にあった} {hate to omit "while their houses burnt down" here}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.96,0:12:08.75,Narrator,,0,0,0,,However...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.88,0:12:13.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Listen. Your suffering might seem never-ending now,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.17,0:12:17.51,Default,,0,0,0,,but as long as you carry on with enough faith in you, you'll always have brighter days up ahead. {ちゃんと信心さえ貫いていけば 必ず幸せになれる}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.63,0:12:21.35,Default,,0,0,0,,You shouldn't think it's all about you alone! {目分一人だけのことじやない}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.35,0:12:25.64,Default,,0,0,0,,This kid's future happiness and everything \Nalso hinges on your faith.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.64,0:12:31.61,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you say? \NWill you be able to persevere for some more? {どうだ 辛抱強くやれるがね ?}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.61,0:12:34.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah... Yes! I'll do it...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.40,0:12:37.11,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm counting on you.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.66,0:12:44.24,Default,,0,0,0,,If you ever find yourself in dire straits again, \Nfeel free to come see me anytime. {また困つたことがぁったらいつでも訪ねてきなさぃ}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.24,0:12:46.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay! Thank you ever so much!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.17,0:12:53.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Cheer up, will you?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.56,0:13:11.56,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\bord0\blur0.5\c&HDCE5EF&\3c&H9E7D32&}Nakano Station {中野駅}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.56,0:13:16.44,Thought,,0,0,0,,Today must be the day I take the first step \Ntowards inheriting my late mentor's mantle. {/the torch from my mentor} {/carrying on with ...'s legacy/cause/work left uncompleted at death} {今日こそ恩師の遺業を継ぐ第一歩の日にしなくては}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.44,0:13:17.94,Thought,,0,0,0,,{Day of }First step.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.32,0:13:19.70,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Year when the war ended,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.70,0:13:21.74,Narrator,,0,0,0,,November 18th. {終戦の年の11月18日}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.70,0:13:25.91,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\bord0\blur0.5\c&HFFFDFF&}November 18, 1945\N{\fs20} Memorial service for the first anniversary of {first president }Makiguchi Tsunesaburo's death
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.74,0:13:26.33,Narrator,,0,0,0,,A memorial {Buddhist }service was held for Makiguchi Tsunesaburo, the founder of Soka Kyoiku Gakkai,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.33,0:13:29.41,Narrator,,0,0,0,,on the first anniversary of his death. {創価教育学会初代会長・牧口常三郎の一周忌追善法要が営まれた}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.87,0:13:35.92,Thought,,0,0,0,,Sensei, I still remember that day in June of 1943. {先生あれは確か昭和18 年の6月でしたね} {lib}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.96,0:13:40.34,Thought,,0,0,0,,Upon the summons from the religious affairs council,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.34,0:13:45.43,Thought,,0,0,0,,we were hurriedly following Makiguchi-sensei uphill to the Taisekiji Temple. {宗務院の呼び出しにより急きょ私たちは牧口先生に従って大石寺に登山した}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.43,0:13:46.81,Thought,,0,0,0,,At that time, the sect
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.81,0:13:48.64,Thought,,0,0,0,,feared the oppression from the military,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.64,0:13:52.06,Thought,,0,0,0,,so to placate the authorities, the prayer book text was altered. {no clue what's 御観念文 but I see it being used as "prayer text"; Gokanmon (Buddhist scriptures)} {あの当時宗門は軍部の弾圧を恐れ権力に迎合して御観念文を改ざんし}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.06,0:13:54.65,Thought,,0,0,0,,We've effaced some important verses from the scriptures,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.65,0:13:58.44,Thought,,0,0,0,,thus committing an act of blasphemy against Daishonin's teachings. {御書の重要御文を削除して大聖人の教えに反する 謗法行為を犯していた - apparently he means "important prayers/sentences/holy writings removed from nichiren's letters" but it's not the same as "scriptures" it seems and "nichiren's letters" is a mouthful, but saying "gosho" is overcomplicating things}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.44,0:14:02.11,Thought,,0,0,0,,And on top of that, something even darker... {actually just "there was another thing" but no clue what he means} {その上に加えてこともあろうに。。。}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.53,0:14:02.11,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\bord0\blur0.5\c&HFFF1FE&}Head Temple Taisekiji {大石寺 宗務院}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.45,0:14:07.24,Default,,0,0,0,,...So I hope you understand why the military is also strung out because of this. {…そういうわけで 軍部も非常に神経をとがらせている}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.24,0:14:12.62,Default,,0,0,0,,If you keep slandering our divine amulets, \Nyou might just end up pouring oil on the fire. {神札を謗法払いするのは火に油を注ぐような結果になりかねない}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.63,0:14:22.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, Makiguchi-san, how about you and your Society accept our amulets just in case? {unsure, "tentatively; for the time being" also makes sense} {学会も一応神札を受けるようにしたらどうでしょう} {I feel that "accept/receive" isn't strong enough a word, as it'll imply hallowing it next}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.65,0:14:39.32,Default,,0,0,0,,We will never accept your amulets!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.74,0:14:48.08,Default,,0,0,0,,It is not the ruin of a single sect that I lament. {私が嘆くのは一宗が滅びることではない}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.41,0:14:50.99,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the utter destruction of an entire nation. {一国が滅び去ることだ}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.99,0:14:55.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I solemnly fear the sorrow of Daishonin, \Nthe founder of our sect. {宗祖大聖人の悲しみを私はひたすら恐れるのだ}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.25,0:14:59.67,Default,,0,0,0,,More than ever, the time is now \Nto try and rectify the leaders' ways. {https://k-dic.sokanet.jp/%E5%9B%BD%E4%B8%BB%E8%AB%AB%E6%9A%81%EF%BC%88%E3%81%93%E3%81%8F%E3%81%97%E3%82%85%E3%81%8B%E3%82%93%E3%81%8E%E3%82%87%E3%81%86%EF%BC%89/ - To enlighten and reprimand leaders' delusions regarding important national issues.  - literally "national admonishing dawn" or "the enlightenment of leadership"}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.67,0:15:02.21,Default,,0,0,0,,What in the world are we afraid of, then? {今こそ国家諫暁の時ではないか 一体何を恐れているのだ!}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.71,0:15:05.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Toda-kun, what are your thoughts on it?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.30,0:15:09.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Sensei, I will fight for this cause like my life depends on it! {先生 戸田は命を懸けて戦います }
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.56,0:15:14.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Come what may, I'll be by your side in everything you do. {何がどうなろうと戸田はどこまでも先生のお供をさせていただきます! - accompany to wherever you go}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.98,0:15:15.85,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.06,0:15:20.98,Thought,,0,0,0,,After that, the authorities began oppressing us in earnest. {あの後国家権力による弾圧が始まり}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.98,0:15:25.90,Thought,,0,0,0,,Sensei was arrested in Shimoda, Izu{/of the Izu province} on the same day, July 6th.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.90,0:15:28.45,Thought,,0,0,0,,I was also arrested at my home in Shirokanedai
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.45,0:15:32.37,Thought,,0,0,0,,on charges of violating the Peace Preservation Law and lese-majesty. {私も治安維持法違反と不敬罪の容疑で白金台の自宅で逮捕されました}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.70,0:15:36.87,Thought,,0,0,0,,Which makes that \Nthe last time I saw Sensei. {そしてあの時が先生とお会いする最後となったのですね}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.37,0:15:42.63,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\bord0\blur0.5\c&HFCD3E2&}September, 1943\NMetropolitan Police Department, Internal Detention Center {昭和18年9月 警視庁內 留置場}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.96,0:15:39.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Come out. You'll be interrogated. {出ろ 取り調ベだ}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.28,0:16:08.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that you, Makiguchi-sensei?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.66,0:16:11.70,Default,,0,0,0,,It's you, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.12,0:16:14.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Makiguchi-sensei!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.54,0:16:16.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Toda-kun?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.62,0:16:19.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Move it! Who said you can stop?! {こら! 立ち止まるんではなぃ}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.12,0:16:20.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah! Makiguchi-sensei!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.30,0:16:24.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Asshole!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.13,0:16:25.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Start walking!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.26,0:16:27.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Sensei!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.47,0:16:32.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Please! Don't be harsh on him! {/Just take care of his health} {どうがお体だけは 大切に ! - could be he's saying "take care of yourself" to sensei, but that's kinda poinless, he ain't got much means to dothat}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.64,0:16:37.64,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\bord0\blur0.5\c&HFFE6F7&\fade(0,400)} January, 1945 \NSugamo, Tokyo Detention Center, Interrogation Room {昭和20年1月 巣鴨 東京拘置所 取調室}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.64,0:16:39.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Toda-san, it's about time you've come clean about your guilt. {戸田さんよ そろそろ素直に罪を認めたらどうかね}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.65,0:16:41.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Even if you're telling me to come clean,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.61,0:16:44.90,Default,,0,0,0,,I haven't done anything wrong, therefore I can't come clean. {認めろと言ったって 何も悪いことはしていないんだかろ 認めようがない}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.65,0:16:47.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Second verse same as first, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.78,0:16:50.36,Default,,0,0,0,,All your other buddies have pleaded guilty already,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.36,0:16:53.08,Default,,0,0,0,,swore to convert and had their leave long ago. {ぁんたの仲間はみんな罪を認め転向を誓ってとっくにここを出ていったよ}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.08,0:16:55.74,Default,,0,0,0,,You're the only remaining idiot.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.74,0:16:59.96,Default,,0,0,0,,That is not true. \NMakiguchi-sensei also persists. {そんなことはない 牧ロ先生が厳然としていらっしゃる - no clue what he means}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.46,0:17:02.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Makiguchi is dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.17,0:17:03.84,Default,,0,0,0,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.22,0:17:12.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Sensei...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.76,0:17:16.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Sensei!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.85,0:17:19.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Makiguchi-sensei!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.56,0:17:26.36,Default,,0,0,0,,A great many yielded to the pressure \Nand disavowed our cause. {多くの者が弾圧に屈して退転するなかで} {retrogression (to a lower level of religious practice)​}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.36,0:17:28.94,Default,,0,0,0,,But President Makiguchi never stepped back,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.94,0:17:32.57,Default,,0,0,0,,and was martyred for his unbending fight against the militaristic authorities. {牧ロ会長は一歩も退かずに軍部国家権力と戦い殉教されました}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.57,0:17:36.70,Default,,0,0,0,,He sacrificed even his precious life \Nto the spread of Lotus Sutra Path. {妙法流布のために尊いその身をささけられたのです - myouhou is not exactly lotus sutra, I think it's a portmaneau word he made up by combining kosen rufu and myouhou}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.79,0:17:41.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Sensei only passed through the prison gate after he died.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.29,0:17:44.63,Default,,0,0,0,,While I, the unworthy disciple of his, made it out alive. {先生は死して獄門を出られた 不肖の弟子の私は 生きて獄門を出た}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.63,0:17:49.13,Default,,0,0,0,,There is, thus, only one thing that I must do next, \Nlying in the plain sight. {私が何をなさねばならぬかは自明の理であります}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.84,0:17:53.39,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm going to say it loud and clear now! {私は今はっきりと申し上げる}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.39,0:17:56.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Even if the entire the world gives up on the Common Path,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.05,0:17:58.64,Default,,0,0,0,,I, Toda Josei, will keep professing it no matter what! {広宣流布は誰がやらなくともこの戸田城聖が必ずいたします - tlc, if we ever find one. I assumed "even if no one else does kosen rufu, I will definitely do it" but very unsure, also suspecting "I will always be there to help anyone spreading the kosen rufu"}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.64,0:18:06.65,Thought,,0,0,0,,My sincere devotion to our cause \Nwasn't shared by a single person there. {tlc as well, 私の真意を感じてくれた者は 誰一人としていなかった… - lit is "feel my true intentions" but that doesn't make sense to me, I'd assume "there wasn't anyone with a faith as strong as mine"}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.78,0:18:17.37,Thought,,0,0,0,,Will I really be able use the Common Path to save the people? {/Will I really be able to save the people \Nwith Common Path this way?}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.42,0:18:27.25,Thought,,0,0,0,,A lion roars alone. {獅子は伴侶を求めず - apparently, some quote from toda or ikeda, in a sense that he must proceed alone, but really toda doesn't strike me as a lion;} {/does not seek allies}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.38,0:18:34.63,Thought,,0,0,0,,That's right. I have to become a lion.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.14,0:18:37.35,Thought,,0,0,0,,Common Path best befits a lion! {/lion's work} {think he means "only lion can handle ..."}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.72,0:18:41.68,Thought,,0,0,0,,Even when I stand all alone, I must inspire unquestionable confidence in people! {also tlc lmao; 一人立つ時人は求めずしてついてくるものだ - assumed he means "if I become a lion, people will follow me without asking any questions" which doesn't really make sense to me and also sounds quite ominous of a positive character, therefore very liberal}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.93,0:18:49.98,Song,,0,0,0,,I now receive the Buddha’s decree, {我今仏の旨をうけ - nobody seems to know what 仏の旨 is}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.98,0:18:57.95,Song,,0,0,0,,Which is his vow to save all through the Lotus{ Sutra} Path. {mystic law is too Greek a term to actually use so I'm translating this as lotus sutra path as in line on 17:32} {妙法流布の大願を}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.66,0:19:05.62,Song,,0,0,0,,I stand proudly alone with my head held high - {高く掲げて一人立つ}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.00,0:19:13.59,Song,,0,0,0,,Friends are hard to come by, foes are numerous. {味方は少なし敵多し}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.39,0:19:21.72,Narrator,,0,0,0,,When 1946 started,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.72,0:19:27.81,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Toda truncated the Society's previous name \Nof Soka Kyoiku Gakkai to just Soka Gakkai.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.39,0:19:26.35,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\c&H252733&\3c&HE0D7DF&\blur1}Soka Gakkai Headquarters
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.81,0:19:31.36,Narrator,,0,0,0,,The new signboard was put up at the Nihon Shogakkan office.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.36,0:19:33.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Sensei, it's a great thing! {could mean anything}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.19,0:19:36.61,Default,,0,0,0,,I feel like my body and mind have been \Nrefreshed and tightened up from this! {なんかこう身も心もしゃきっと引き締まる感じです}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.61,0:19:39.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. It's finally getting a fresh start. {うん いよいよ新しい出発だ - assumed he means "a fresh start/departure; leaving; setting off for society"}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.16,0:19:45.54,Thought,,0,0,0,,There's no reason the Society's goals \Nshould remain limited to education alone. {学会の目的は単に教育だけにとどまるものではない}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.54,0:19:49.96,Thought,,0,0,0,,Politics, economy, culture, and so on - \Nin various fields, constituting life,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.96,0:19:53.59,Thought,,0,0,0,,we must become an omnipresent force \Nthat invigorates the people. {政治経済文化等社会のあらゆる分野にわたって民衆に活力を与えゆく存在とならなくてはならない} {avoiding repeating word "society" here}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.63,0:19:56.59,Thought,,0,0,0,,From this base, we need to start sending
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.59,0:20:01.56,Thought,,0,0,0,,out into the world countless promising men, armed with a great ideal of Lotus Sutra. {本部のこの拠点から妙法の大理念を受けた多くの人材が続々と巣立っていかなければ国を救うことなどできるはずがない…！}{no clue why he says "this base of headquarter"; liberal bc impossible to split oftherwise + cps hell - had to omit headquarters and "one after another"; also jinzai could be "human resources; personnel" so that'd be like saying "other recruiters for our sect" but not sure}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.56,0:20:04.39,Thought,,0,0,0,,Otherwise, we can't hope to save this country.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.39,0:20:06.94,Thought,,0,0,0,,And those capable, promising men... {here he says "talented/capable" twice which is what made me think previous jinzai could act. be "personnel"}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.64,0:20:10.86,Thought,,0,0,0,,Right. The youth. It could only be the youth.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.82,0:20:13.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Mishima-kun.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.73,0:20:18.24,Default,,0,0,0,,So? Are you finding that {place \Nat }Editor-in-Chief's desk comfortable? {level of comfort (of objects you sit on) - you don't exactly sit on a desk} {編集長のデスクの座り心地は?}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.11,0:20:22.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. Thank you for your continued support. {とうごさいます おがけさまで が}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.74,0:20:25.25,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm counting on you for our next project. {次の企画 よろしく頼みますよ}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.25,0:20:25.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.66,0:20:29.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Is this book performing well? {どうだい この本は ?}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.00,0:20:33.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. It gained an enormous traction already. \NWe barely manage to keep up with the demand. {/putting them out with a great vigor} {はい もう大変な評判です\Nすごい勢いで出てます}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.46,0:20:38.13,Default,,0,0,0,,So I thought. These days, all and sundry, \Nyoung men in particular,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.13,0:20:42.47,Default,,0,0,0,,are jumping ecstatically into the feast of democracy they've never tasted before. {not a particularly straightforward analogy but I can't think of any simpler one in English} {今は誰も彼も 特に若者はだ食べたこともない民主主義というごちそうに夢中になって飛び付いている}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.47,0:20:46.48,Default,,0,0,0,,But let me tell you. \NThis is not what true democracy looks like. {だがね 真実の民主主義とはこんなもんじゃないんだよ}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.47,0:20:44.97,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\fade(0,200)\c&H071B33&\b0\blur0.4\bord\3c&H93ABCB&} Philosophy & History {原理&歷史 ... - can't get the middle line} \NNihon Shogakkan
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.31,0:20:48.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.98,0:20:51.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Democracy in the true sense of the word {本当の意味の民主主義は}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.98,0:20:57.19,Default,,0,0,0,,cannot be achieved through merely replacing the ruling party \Nand reforming the societal structures. {単なる政治機構や社会体制の変革だけで出来上がるもんじゃない}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.19,0:20:59.53,Default,,0,0,0,,It must first establish itself in people's minds.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.53,0:21:02.74,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the starting point, the foundation of democracy. {個人の内側からの確立それが出発点であり土台となるんだよ}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.33,0:21:04.87,Default,,0,0,0,,So? Are you following? {/do yo uunderstand}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.41,0:21:11.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Establish itself in the minds of individuals \Nby means of Human Revolution!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.75,0:21:13.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Kiyohara-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.92,0:21:14.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.21,0:21:18.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Listen. This is your own Human Revolution. \NI have mine...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.17,0:21:22.84,Default,,0,0,0,,And Yamadaira-kun has his! All must undergo their individual Human Revolution.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.84,0:21:26.52,Default,,0,0,0,,That's where the democracy is being born \Nand that's what it boils down to. {そこから民主主義は始まり そこに帰結するんだよ}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.02,0:21:29.52,Default,,0,0,0,,It's never just about institutions and policies. {制度や政策だけの問題じゃない}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.98,0:21:33.90,Default,,0,0,0,,It's about people! \NIt's about lighting the way for people! {lit is "shining/shedding/hitting light on humans"} {人間なんだよ 人間に光を当てることなんだよ}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.94,0:21:37.53,Default,,0,0,0,,It's these people,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.53,0:21:42.70,Default,,0,0,0,,suffering greatly from this defeat in the war, who need someone to light the way for them! {敗戦によって苦しみ抜いているこの人たちにこそ光を当てていがなければならないのだ!} {/show them the light}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.12,0:21:47.70,Thought,,0,0,0,,The youth are earnestly pursuing the Buddha Dharma. {no clue what he means} {青年たちが真剣に仏法を求めようとしている}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.41,0:21:52.50,Thought,,0,0,0,,I must do my utmost to teach these young men \Nthe greatness of the Buddha Dharma. {この青年たちに仏法の偉大さを 何としても教えなければ…}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.50,0:21:54.00,Thought,,0,0,0,,Maybe my perfect chance is now...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.42,0:21:55.79,Thought,,0,0,0,,All right. Let's go for it!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.26,0:22:03.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Yamadaira-kun, Kiyohara-san, I'm doing it! \NCourse of lectures on the Lotus Sutra. {sounds like he wants to give one right now but actually gotta means "lets start giving lectures"} {始めるぞ法華経の講義を}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.10,0:22:09.27,Thought,,0,0,0,,Toda-sensei is finally starting to give lectures on Lotus Sutra. {戸田先生がいよいよ法華経の講義をしてくださる}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.27,0:22:10.56,Thought,,0,0,0,,I've never been this happy!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.98,0:22:14.90,Thought,,0,0,0,,I should probably also tell Izumida-san \Nand gather as many people as I can! {泉田さんにも知らせて一人でも多く人を集めなくては…}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.90,0:22:19.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh? Toda-sensei is giving lectures? That's just amazing!
Comment: 0,0:22:14.90,0:22:19.40,Sign,,0,0,0,,Forest Villa {unsure, maybe "Hayashiso" or something, 林荘}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.40,0:22:23.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's split the work now and send express mail \Nto everyone whose address we know! {手分けして 住所の分かっているところへ速達を出しましようよ}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.74,0:22:27.49,Default,,0,0,0,,But many evacuated because their homes \Nburned down during the war... {戦災で家が焼けて疎開している人もいるし}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.49,0:22:29.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Will they be able to receive it? {/be delivered properly}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:29.37,0:22:32.25,Default,,0,0,0,,No point worrying about that right now!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.25,0:22:34.87,Default,,0,0,0,,For the time being, let's just do whatever we can! {ともかくできるかきりのことをしなくちゃ}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:34.87,0:22:37.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Agreed! Let's do just that!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:37.21,0:22:41.17,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Kiyohara Katsu, {working as }an elementary school teacher, \Nwas the Society's {young }female division leader. {doesn't say society, assumed they mean this} {清原かつは小学校の教員を勤める若手の女性リーダー}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:41.67,0:22:43.84,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Izumida Tame was the wife of a soldier
Dialogue: 0,0:22:43.84,0:22:47.18,Narrator,,0,0,0,,deployed in the South, who was still considered missing in action. {泉田ためは軍人の妻ご 夫は南方に出征したまましIまだ生死不明であった}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:48.18,0:22:54.14,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Both used to be Makiguchi's disciples \Nand managed to maintain a pure faith. {2人は共に牧口門下生として純真な信仰を貫いていた}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.06,0:22:58.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh? Isn't that Kiyohara-san?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:58.82,0:23:00.69,Default,,0,0,0,,My, Konishi-san!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:04.20,0:23:06.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Eh? Chairman Toda? {戸田理事長が?}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.70,0:23:11.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. His company is located in Nishi-Kanda, \Nand that's also where the new headquarters are. {会社が西神田にあってそこを新しい本部にして}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:11.45,0:23:14.46,Default,,0,0,0,,There, he keeps rebuilding the Society brick by brick. {学会再建の活動を進めていらっしゃるわ}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:14.46,0:23:17.46,Default,,0,0,0,,I had no idea! \NBoy, did I miss him!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.46,0:23:21.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah! And this coming Monday, \NSensei will be giving a lecture on Lotus Sutra! {今度の月曜日に先生の法華経の講義があるの}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:21.38,0:23:22.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you coming? {いらっしゃらない？}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.46,0:23:25.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes! I would absolutely love to join! {ぜひとも参加させてもらうよ}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.18,0:23:28.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Seki-kun, who is an elementary school teacher just like us,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.43,0:23:30.85,Default,,0,0,0,,also works in Kamata, so I'll bring him along! {僕らと同じく小学校の教員をやっている関君彼も蒲田にいるから一緒に連れていくよ}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.85,0:23:33.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Really? Wow, I'm so glad.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.31,0:23:39.48,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Soka Gakkai makes a new precipitous start \Ntowards the Common Path. {広宣流布に向かって新たおスタートを切った創価学会}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.48,0:23:40.98,Narrator,,0,0,0,,At his new headquarters,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.98,0:23:45.53,Narrator,,0,0,0,,in the same building as Nihon Shogakkan, Toda began lecturing on the Lotus Sutra. {その新本部・日本正学館で戸田による法華経講義が開始された}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:46.11,0:23:49.20,Default,,0,0,0,,In short, my lecture on the Lotus Sutra boils down to this:
Dialogue: 0,0:23:49.20,0:23:53.04,Default,,0,0,0,,What exactly is Daishonin's "Nam Myoho Renge Kyo" about? {/what kind of thing} {法華経の講義といっても要するに大聖人様の南無妙法蓮華経とはいかなるものか}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:53.04,0:23:55.04,Default,,0,0,0,,That's really all you need to know. {それが分がればいいのです}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:55.04,0:24:01.38,Default,,0,0,0,,We start with the basics - first, what does "Nam" stand for in Nam Myoho Renge Kyo? {南無妙法蓮華経の南無とはどぅいう意味が}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:01.38,0:24:03.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Sadly, it has nothing to do with ham. {deadpun, lit: It's not to say the south doesn't exist - namu is south}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.55,0:24:05.55,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:05.55,0:24:09.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Nam is a word from Sanskrit, \Nwhich translates to "devotion to Buddha." {lit: when translated into Japanese word of Chinese origin; Sino-Japanese word, it is devoting one's life to the Buddha; obeying the Buddha's teachings - same root as "namashite"​}{南無は梵語であり漢語では帰命と訳します}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.55,0:24:12.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Devote - literally "dedicate by a vow." \NAre you following? {okay, this is literally untranslatable without a TL note: he breaks up the kanji to explain the combination; lit: devotion - to accredit life; 帰命命を帰する分かりますね}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:12.43,0:24:13.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:12.64,0:24:13.43,Overlap,,0,0,0,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:14.14,0:24:16.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, when we say "Nam,"
Dialogue: 0,0:24:16.06,0:24:20.06,Default,,0,0,0,,it means we believe in Buddha \Nand offer our bodies and souls together to him. {ですがら南無するといえば身も心も共に信じてささげることを意味します}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.07,0:24:27.57,Default,,0,0,0,,As for Myoho Renge Kyo part, it refers to the 28 chapters of Gautama Buddha's Lotus Sutra. {believing https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lotus_Sutra}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:27.57,0:24:31.07,Default,,0,0,0,,In the present Latter Day of the Law, Daishonin's Buddhism
Dialogue: 0,0:24:31.07,0:24:34.08,Default,,0,0,0,,was mainly defined by Nam Myoho Renge Kyo. {unsure what he means: 末法の現在にあっては日蓮大聖人の南無妙法蓮華経の仏法になります}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:34.08,0:24:38.00,Default,,0,0,0,,The line we must draw clearly and firmly here is... {ここで深くはっきりと留意しなければならないことは - unsure what to make of "heed deep and clear"}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:38.00,0:24:40.71,Default,,0,0,0,,If we don't uphold Daishonin's Buddhism,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:40.71,0:24:44.09,Default,,0,0,0,,the living creatures of the Latter Day of the Law cannot be saved.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:45.05,0:24:49.09,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\bord0\blur0.5\c&HFFF5F2&\fade(400,0)} On the next {day of }lecture... {講義}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:45.30,0:24:48.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Next would be Seki-kun's part. \NRead it for us, will you? {次のところを関くん 読んでくれないか}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:48.05,0:24:48.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:51.05,0:24:52.51,Default,,0,0,0,,"Siddhartha became Buddha. {technically "Tathagata is Shakyamuni" - a very informative sentence to anyone unfamiliar with buddhism, but I refuse to introduce more complications to something otherwise so simple at this point}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:52.51,0:24:55.60,Default,,0,0,0,,And by extension, various Buddhas \Nof ten directions and three times. {「如来とは釈尊総じては十方三世の諸仏なり」}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:56.10,0:24:57.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Particularly, his true form..." {「別しては…」}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:57.68,0:25:01.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Hm. Their drive to seek the truth becomes stronger and stronger. {求道の息吹がますます高まってきているな}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:01.69,0:25:04.69,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\bord0\blur0.5\c&HFAF3FC&}Furthermore, on the next lecture...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:02.69,0:25:06.32,Narrator,,0,0,0,,With every session, the number of listeners increased. {回を重ねるごとに受講者の数は増し}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:06.32,0:25:08.45,Narrator,,0,0,0,,The air was thick in Nihon Shogakkan hall,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:08.45,0:25:12.70,Narrator,,0,0,0,,heated by both the passion of the one giving the lectures {sounds almost as if he wasn't the only one giving the lectures}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:12.70,0:25:15.29,Narrator,,0,0,0,,and those listening intently, trying not to miss a word. {日本正学館の広間は講義をする者その一言をも聞き漏らすまいとする者の熱い思いがあふれこいた}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:17.08,0:25:21.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, Sensei, if we are also tasked with a noble mission of saving the people,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:21.79,0:25:24.59,Default,,0,0,0,,does that make us the Bodhisattvas of the Earth?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:24.59,0:25:27.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course it does. No doubt about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:27.76,0:25:32.59,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you guys think? \NCan you feel that you {\i1}are{\i0} the Bodhisattvas of the Earth? {どうだい君たち 自分がその地涌の菩薩だと自覚できるがい?}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:33.39,0:25:34.85,Default,,0,0,0,,No, not really...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:35.31,0:25:38.10,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:38.10,0:25:41.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. It's a bit hard to tell on your own. {そう 自分ではなかなか分がらないものだ}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:41.60,0:25:45.73,Default,,0,0,0,,But as Daishonin-sama put it once, \N"If it wasn't for the {appearance of the }Bodhisattvas of the Earth,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:45.73,0:25:47.69,Default,,0,0,0,,this chant would've fallen into oblivion." {I have no clue what's this about, but from what I could gather, nichiren was oppressed and everyone chanted old chant or didn't chant at all until bod. of the earth appeared and started chanting it too, otherwise this chant would've been hard to disseminate}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:47.69,0:25:50.28,Default,,0,0,0,,By saying so, he decreed it sternly:
Dialogue: 0,0:25:50.28,0:25:52.95,Default,,0,0,0,,in the Latter Day of the Law,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:52.95,0:25:56.95,Default,,0,0,0,,only those who chant Nam Myoho Renge Kyo get to become Bodhisattvas of the Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:56.95,0:25:58.70,Default,,0,0,0,,That's something to be proud of!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:59.70,0:26:02.67,Default,,0,0,0,,We, my friends, are the Bodhisattvas of the Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:02.67,0:26:05.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Wearing some rags, with a constantly growling stomach...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:05.71,0:26:06.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Konishi-kun,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:07.71,0:26:08.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Seki-kun,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:09.30,0:26:10.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Kiyohara-san as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:11.30,0:26:15.14,Default,,0,0,0,,It is beyond doubt for me \Nthat you are {exactly }the Bodhisattvas of the Earth. {間違いなく君たちこそが地涌の菩薩なんだよ}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:15.14,0:26:16.30,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:16.64,0:26:20.56,Default,,0,0,0,,That's something I want everyone of you \Nto realize clearly today. {今日はみんなにこのことをはっきりと自覚してもらいたいのだ}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:21.02,0:26:22.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you do that, friends?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:22.56,0:26:23.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:22.69,0:26:23.56,Overlap,,0,0,0,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:26.06,0:26:29.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Chairman! Thank you so much. {理事長 ありがとうございました}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:29.48,0:26:30.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't mention it.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:30.94,0:26:34.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Actually, I'd like to organize a roundtable discussion. {実は座談会を開きたいと思っているんです}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:34.70,0:26:37.99,Default,,0,0,0,,So I was wondering if I could get you to join us. {理事長に来ていただくわけにはいかないでしょうか?}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:37.99,0:26:41.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh? A roundtable discussion? Good, I like it! When? {ほう 座談会を… よし 行こう! いつだ?}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:42.29,0:26:44.17,Default,,0,0,0,,This coming Sunday night. {今度の日曜日の夜です}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:48.17,0:26:52.17,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\bord0\blur0.5\c&HFEFEFE&}Konishi's house in Kamata {蒲田 小西家}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:49.46,0:26:53.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh? I see this place was spared the ravages of war.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:53.55,0:26:56.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. The Great Buddha was kind enough to protect it. {はい 御本専様に守られました}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:57.05,0:27:00.60,Default,,0,0,0,,My, it's been a truly long while. \NHas everyone been doing well? {いや しばらくでございます 皆さん 元気でしたか?}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:00.60,0:27:02.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes! We're all fine!
Dialogue: 0,0:27:02.02,0:27:03.60,Default,,0,0,0,,We're ready for action again! {もう 張り切ってやってます - not sure what he means, maybe "regained ... after the war" maybe "were waiting and are eager to start"}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:03.60,0:27:05.60,Default,,0,0,0,,I see, I see. Good to know.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:06.73,0:27:11.73,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Thus, the first roundtable meeting after the reconstruction of the Society was held in Kamata.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:11.73,0:27:15.03,Narrator,,0,0,0,,The roundtable-centered activities that had been a tradition since the times
Dialogue: 0,0:27:15.03,0:27:17.62,Narrator,,0,0,0,,of the first president, Makiguchi, were revived. {牧口初代会長時代からの伝統であった座談会中心の活動が復活した}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:18.58,0:27:21.33,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Young men from the local community gathered at a house
Dialogue: 0,0:27:21.33,0:27:25.46,Narrator,,0,0,0,,in Morigasaki, near the venue where Toda was attending. {戸田が出席している会場に近く森ヶ崎のとある家に地域の青年たちが集まっていた}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:26.25,0:27:28.54,Narrator,,0,0,0,,They were the members of the Reading Circle. {読書サークルのメンバーである}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:29.00,0:27:32.30,Narrator,,0,0,0,,As the established system of values collapsed
Dialogue: 0,0:27:32.30,0:27:36.05,Narrator,,0,0,0,,due to the defeat in the war, people earnestly searched for how they should live now. {敗戦によって既成の価値観が崩壊する中で人々は“いかに生きるべきか”を真剣に模索し}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:36.05,0:27:39.39,Narrator,,0,0,0,,They actively sought to absorb the new knowledge.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:40.60,0:27:45.85,Narrator,,0,0,0,,There was among them a young man quietly listening to his friends from the very front. {最前から仲間の話に静かに耳を傾けている青年がいた}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:40.60,0:27:43.60,Sign,,0,0,0,,Iwanami Bunko:{publisher's name} \NRepresentative Men of Japan {https://ja.wikipedia.org/wiki/%E4%BB%A3%E8%A1%A8%E7%9A%84%E6%97%A5%E6%9C%AC%E4%BA%BA / https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Uchimura_Kanz%C5%8D#Works}{代表的日本人 岩波文庫}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:46.39,0:27:51.77,Narrator,,0,0,0,,The young man seemed to reside in deep contemplation, searching for something intently.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:56.07,0:27:58.66,Default,,0,0,0,,We've had quite a productive reading session today. {今日の読書会充実してたね}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:58.66,0:28:02.91,Default,,0,0,0,,I feel that I have something in common with the way of life of Uchimura Kanzo,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:02.91,0:28:04.87,Default,,0,0,0,,who became a Christian. {僕はキリス卜教徒になった内村鑑三の生き方に何か通じるものを感じるんだ - unsure what he means}
Dialogue: 0,0:28:07.37,0:28:10.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh? You've started reading it already?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:10.04,0:28:13.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Miki Kiyoshi's Notes on the Theory of Life. It looks awfully difficult. {もう読み始めてるのか 三木清の「人生論ノー卜」 難しそうだな} {https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kiyoshi_Miki#List_of_works}
Dialogue: 0,0:28:13.13,0:28:15.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. I'm having a hard time reading this.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:15.63,0:28:20.05,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm a somewhat slow-paced fella, \Nso I can barely read one book a month. {僕はペースが遅いから月に一冊がやっとだけど}
Dialogue: 0,0:28:20.05,0:28:24.47,Default,,0,0,0,,They call you Bookworm Yamamoto-kun, \Nso you probably read like five or six, right? {山本君は〝本の虫"といわれるぐらいだがら 5~6冊は読むんだろう ?}
Dialogue: 0,0:28:24.47,0:28:25.64,Default,,0,0,0,,No, I wouldn't say...
Dialogue: 0,0:28:26.64,0:28:33.65,Narrator,,0,0,0,,The youngest of the group, \Nthis teenager's name was Yamamoto Shinichi. {グループの中で一番年少のこの若者は一名前を“山本伸一”といった}
Dialogue: 0,0:28:33.65,0:28:36.65,Narrator,,0,0,0,,By day he toiled for a tiny printing company,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:36.65,0:28:40.66,Narrator,,0,0,0,,and by night, he attended \NOriental Commerce {High }School in Kanda-Misakicho.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:41.82,0:28:43.95,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:43.95,0:28:45.70,Default,,0,0,0,,How does it look for your health? {どうなの 体の調子は ?}
Dialogue: 0,0:28:45.70,0:28:49.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I seem to get a bit of a fever in the evenings, but I'll be fine. {夕方になるとちょっと熱が出るようだけど でも 大丈夫だ}
Dialogue: 0,0:28:49.54,0:28:50.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't push yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:51.17,0:28:51.79,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:51.79,0:28:55.13,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Yamamoto already had an ailing chest. {山本青年は胸を患っていた - no clue what's this about and couldn't find any info on daisaku ikeda's health when he was young; also no clue why she always adds "young man" before his name}
Dialogue: 0,0:28:55.71,0:28:59.13,Narrator,,0,0,0,,He became ill while working at a munitions factory in Kamata. {蒲田の軍需工場で働いている時に発病し}
Dialogue: 0,0:28:59.13,0:29:04.35,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Presently, he takes medications from the hospital \Nto stave off the progression of disease. {/hamper the progress ...} {今は病院からもらう薬を服用して病気の進行を抑えていた}
Dialogue: 0,0:29:04.81,0:29:10.52,Narrator,,0,0,0,,The doctors' diagnosis was that he probably won't even live to 26. {医者からは「26歳までは持たないだろう」と診断されていたのである}
Dialogue: 0,0:29:17.86,0:29:22.66,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Yamamoto and his friends often strolled along Morigasaki Beach,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:22.66,0:29:25.79,Narrator,,0,0,0,,talking literature and arguing philosophy. {山本青年は友人としばしば森ヶ崎海岸を散策しともに文学を語り哲学を論じ合った}
Dialogue: 0,0:29:26.49,0:29:30.21,Narrator,,0,0,0,,The discussion was endless on questions such as "What is a patriot in this day and age?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:30.21,0:29:32.83,Narrator,,0,0,0,,What is the criterion for good and bad?"
Dialogue: 0,0:29:32.83,0:29:35.17,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Finally, "What is the true and righteous life?" - {“今の時代の愛国者とは 善悪の基準とはー”“真実の正しい人生とは何か”と議論は果てしなく続いたが}
Dialogue: 0,0:29:35.17,0:29:39.09,Narrator,,0,0,0,,They didn't have a single spiritual foothold in sight. {何一つ明確な精神支柱とはならなかった - hope she means "they didn't have a guide/point of reference to figure out these quesrions"}
Dialogue: 0,0:29:42.34,0:29:48.06,Default,,0,0,0,,In the end, I've made up my mind on trying Christianity. Are you coming along? {結論として僕はキリスト教信仰してみようと決心したんだ 君も一緒に…? }
Dialogue: 0,0:29:48.47,0:29:52.56,Default,,0,0,0,,No. Honestly, I don't feel drawn to Christianity. {いや 僕はキリスト教に引かれるものはない}
Dialogue: 0,0:29:52.56,0:29:57.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I will still try to pursue my own path \Nin a way unique to me. {僕は僕自身のやり方で自分の進むべき道を追求してみるつもりだ}
Dialogue: 0,0:29:57.48,0:30:03.95,Song,,0,0,0,,With my friend by the shore, Morigasaki
Dialogue: 0,0:30:03.95,0:30:09.83,Song,,0,0,0,,Pungent seaside smell, waves withdrawing {岸辺に友と森ヶ崎\N磯の香高く波かえし}
Dialogue: 0,0:30:10.29,0:30:16.92,Song,,0,0,0,,Nineteen-year-old boys, struggling to choose a path
Dialogue: 0,0:30:16.92,0:30:22.72,Song,,0,0,0,,Philosophy talk as the hours go by {十九の青春道まよい\N哲学語り時は過ぐ}
Dialogue: 0,0:30:22.72,0:30:30.27,Song,,0,0,0,,Always troubled being poor, my friend utters:
Dialogue: 0,0:30:30.27,0:30:35.90,Song,,0,0,0,,"The way of Christ is the one I'll follow" {友は悩めり貧しけれ\N基督の道われ行くと}
Dialogue: 0,0:30:35.90,0:30:49.41,Song,,0,0,0,,Eyes flashing keen in the moonlight, \NTo that firm heartbeat, the waves roll in... {瞳きびしく月映えて\Nつよき鼓動に波寄せり}
Dialogue: 0,0:30:49.41,0:30:54.17,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Thus, Yamamoto Shinichi's deep contemplations kept piling up. {なおも山本伸一青年の深い思索が重ねられていく - unsure what she means}
Dialogue: 0,0:30:54.62,0:30:59.42,Narrator,,0,0,0,,But before long, he would find himself overwhelmed, when time comes
Dialogue: 0,0:30:59.42,0:31:02.17,Narrator,,0,0,0,,for his fateful encounter with Toda Josei. {そして劇的な戸田城聖との運命の出会いの時をやがて迎えることになるのである - complicated wording and I don't understand all of it}
